sense.name: (cause to) come to rest on a surface
sense.commentary: NOTE: The surface does not need to be stated as in the last sentence.
sense.examples: The Apollo 13 landed in the Pacific Ocean. It landed four miles away from the ship USS Iwo Jima. A pirate ship landed on the shore near a small village. Is it true that an alien space ship landed in Liverpool? How 400,000 people landed Apollo 11 on the moon. Ash from the volcano travelled hundreds of miles to land on our house. The monkey has landed.

sense.name: experience, receive or gain something important
sense.examples: How did Jerry land the big funding dollars? Laura Vandervoort has landed the prestigious role of Supergirl. You've landed the job, now negotiate the salary. She landed a gorgeous and powerful CEO husband. Rusty landed the biggest brown trout of the decade. The greyhound rescue group helps the retired dogs land on their feet.

sense.name: deliver a blow
sense.examples: Rayne landed another solid punch, sending his opponent staggering. Filipovic landed several solid kicks to Larry's sides and legs.

sense.name: shoot at and force to come down
sense.examples: The enemy landed several of our fighters.

sense.name: (finally) do something or be somewhere
sense.examples: What happens when friends land up in your city and want to hang out all the time? You will land up paying a lot more in a bad credit mortgage loan. Pop-up adds could land you in jail.

sense.name: block with earth, as after a landslide
